    <briefdescription>
<para>This class emits a signal when a tap gesture occurs that meets the requirements set by the application. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>See <ref refid="classDali_1_1TapGestureDetector_1a8d02d5ebc21368d50be8474db68e655c" kindref="member">TapGestureDetector::SetMinimumTapsRequired</ref> See <ref refid="classDali_1_1TapGestureDetector_1a45dbc7a3cdcc219fa4674ad1a772ca4b" kindref="member">TapGestureDetector::SetMaximumTapsRequired</ref></para>
<para>A <ref refid="classDali_1_1TapGesture" kindref="compound">TapGesture</ref> is a discrete gesture, which means it does not have any state information attached to it. Please see <ref refid="classDali_1_1TapGesture" kindref="compound">TapGesture</ref> for more information.</para>
<para>The application programmer can use this gesture detector as follows: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1TapGestureDetector_1adca0dd2f8a66bf3181597b45c4d18da2" kindref="member">TapGestureDetector</ref><sp/>detector<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1TapGestureDetector_1a5cb1497c9147408eb2508127f8af74c9" kindref="member">TapGestureDetector::New</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">detector.Attach(myActor);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">detector.DetectedSignal().Connect(</highlight><highlight class="keyword">this</highlight><highlight class="normal">,<sp/>&amp;MyApplication::OnTap);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>@SINCE_1_0.0 <simplesect kind="note"><para>Multi-touch taps (two or more points of contact with the surface) are not currently supported. However, multiple taps (double &amp; triple tap etc.) are supported.</para>
</simplesect>
